parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected loss of control
and inability to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries. Additionally, fuel fumes can enter the passenger cabin, posing a health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Fuel smell or fumes inside the passenger cabin
fuel leak visible under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Marelli ignition system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing harm to occupants.
symptoms: Loss of ignition on the right bank of cylinders
engine continues to run on the left bank cylinders
unburned fuel passes through the right-hand cylinders and ignites in the hot catalytic converter

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the tire sidewall can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tire blows out or explodes
while driving at moderate to high speeds
resulting in loss of control or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank can cause leakage, leading to fuel odors and fumes entering the vehicle, which can be a fire hazard and pose a risk to the occupants.
symptoms: Fuel odor or fumes inside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine smoke can indicate a serious problem, potentially leading to engine failure, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
